gomodel:SYNGO_2878  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"The Endocytic Zone is Stably Positioned Near the PSD\"\n\n13/3/2018 Pim\n- CLTA; clathrin light chain A is used as a marker for Endocytic Zones (EZ's). These are shown to be close to and physically attached to the PSD via the homer and dynamin-3 proteins.. Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 rat embryos ...\"\n- Overexpressed Clathrin A; CLTA is of rat species: \"A mouse placental clone with homology to clathrin LCa complementary DNA was identified in the expressed-sequence-tag database and obtained from American Type Cell Culture, sequenced and found to encode full-length clathrin LCa.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2878" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

